BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
2 fund for the Oklahoma Military Department to be designated the "Base
3 Infrastructure Needs and Development - Schools Revolving Fund",
4 which may also be cited as "BIND – Schools Fund". The fund shall be
5 a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
6 consist of all monies directed for deposit to the fund by law. All
7 monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated
8 and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma Military Department
9 for the purpose established in Subsection B of this section.
10 Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants issued by
11 the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with
12 the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
13 approval and payment.
14 B. There is hereby established within the Oklahoma Military
15 Department the "Base Infrastructure Needs and Development – Schools
16 Program", which may also be cited as the "BIND – Schools Program".
17 The Department shall utilize funds from the BIND – Schools Fund
18 created in Subsection A of this section, alone or in combination
19 with other available funding, to make infrastructure investments,
20 including, but not limited to, new construction, improving common
21 education facilities located on military bases in this state, that
22 will either:
23 1. Decrease the likelihood of military base and other military
24 infrastructure closures in this state, or
